  "prompt": "What is kale called in Hindi or Marathi?",
  "response": "In both Hindi and Marathi, **kale** is typically referred to by its English name, transliterated into the respective scripts:\n\n- **Hindi:** \u0915\u0948\u0932 (Kale)\n- **Marathi:** \u0915\u0947\u0932 (Kale)\n\nSince kale is not traditionally common in Indian cuisine, there isn't a widely recognized native term for it. When discussing similar leafy greens, terms like **\u092a\u093e\u0932\u0915** (palak) for spinach in Hindi or **\u092a\u093e\u0932\u0915**/**\u0936\u093e\u0932\u0947** (palak/shale) in Marathi might be used, but they are not exact equivalents to kale. If you're referring to kale specifically, using the transliterated form is generally understood, especially in urban and cosmopolitan contexts.",
